00051 #if defined(__ASM_386_GCC__)
00052 #define ROTATE_LEFT(X,n)  \
00053     ({ ubyte4 _R = X; __asm __volatile ("rol %1, %0": "=r"(_R) : "i"(n), "0"(_R)); _R;})
00054 #define ROTATE_RIGHT(X,n) \
00055 ({ ubyte4 _R = X; __asm __volatile ("ror %1, %0": "=r"(_R) : "i"(n), "0"(_R)); _R;})
00056 #elif defined(__ASM_PPC__)
00057  /* newer versions of the gcc compiler do that optimization already! */
00058 #define ROTATE_LEFT(X,n) \
00059 ( {ubyte4 _R; __asm __volatile("rotlwi %0, %1, %2": "=r"(_R): "r"(X), "i"(n)); _R; })
00060 #define ROTATE_RIGHT(X,n) \
00061 ( {ubyte4 _R; __asm __volatile("rotrwi %0, %1, %2": "=r"(_R): "r"(X), "i"(n)); _R; })
00062 #elif defined(__xxASM_ARM__)
00063 /* don't enable this for ARM since gcc is able to wrap the rotation operation
00064    as part of some other instruction... like add r1, r2, r7, ror #27 */
00065 #define ROTATE_LEFT(X,n) \
00066 ( {ubyte4 _R; __asm __volatile("mov %0, %1, ror %2": "=r"(_R): "r"(X), "i"(32-n)); _R; })
00067 #define ROTATE_RIGHT(X,n) \
00068 ( {ubyte4 _R; __asm __volatile("mov %0, %1, ror %2": "=r"(_R): "r"(X), "i"(n)); _R; })
00069 #else
00070     /* MIPS does not have rotate instructions */
00071 /* rotate X left n bits */
00072 #define ROTATE_LEFT(X,n)        (((ubyte4)(X) << (n)) | (((ubyte4)X) >> (32-(n))))
00073 #define ROTATE_RIGHT(X,n)       (((ubyte4)(X) >> (n)) | (((ubyte4)(X)) << (32-(n))))
00074 #endif
